==English==
===Expression===
'''I [[stand]] [[correct]]ed'''

# {{idiom}} Said to [[acknowledge]] someone who corrects something that one says or writes that was not correct.
#: ''The Battle of Hastings was fought in 1056.''
#: ''No it wasn't! Look in the textbook!''
#: ''Oh, sorry. '''I stand corrected''' - it was fought in 1066.''

